# Slatepress design system

## Brand tokens

Use these color tokens only. Do not introduce new hex codes without consulting the `premium-web-designer` Claude skill.

```
/* Surfaces */
--cream:       #F5F1E8   /* page canvas - the default surface */
--cream-deep:  #EBE5D4   /* alternating sections, subtle wells */
--white:       #FFFFFF   /* cards, modals, form fields */

/* Hairlines and rules */
--hairline:    #C9C2B1   /* 1px borders, dividers, input outlines */

/* Text */
--ink:         #14181F   /* primary text, near-black with cool undertone */
--ink-soft:    #2A2F39   /* secondary text */
--muted:       #6E6B66   /* tertiary text, labels, eyebrows */

/* Accent - used sparingly, never as decoration */
--amber:       #C2720D   /* primary accent - ochre, on CTAs and ::selection */
--amber-lt:    #E8A84D   /* highlight variant, hover, subtle emphasis */
```

## Type stack

- `--f-serif`: `'Fraunces', Georgia, serif` - display + editorial body
- `--f-sans`: `'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif` - UI, buttons, dense interface text
- `--f-mono`: `'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace` - eyebrows, labels, code, tabular data

## Cardinal rules

- **Cream is the page canvas, NOT pure white.** Pure `#FFF` is reserved for elevated surfaces (cards, modals, form fields). A pure-white page background is a thoughtless-design tell.
- **One accent color, one job.** Amber appears on primary CTAs, `::selection`, focus rings, and at most one emphasis moment per viewport. Never as decoration or area fill.
- **No gradient buttons, no carousels, no Lorem ipsum, no emoji in production UI.**
- **Generous whitespace.** Section padding: 96px mobile, 128px desktop minimum.
- **High contrast.** Body text against canvas should hit WCAG AAA (7:1 ratio). Tertiary text never below AA (4.5:1).
- **Max two type weights per page**, e.g. Fraunces 400 + JetBrains Mono 400. Three is the upper limit.

## When designing or reviewing UI

Defer to the `premium-web-designer` Claude skill (installed globally at `~/.claude/skills/premium-web-designer/`). It encodes the full visual language including the type scale, spacing tokens, motion rules, and quality checklist.

The skill fires automatically when Claude Code is asked to design, redesign, review, or polish any Slatepress surface.
